From 2a29c4caff9ce99f2feae11327b2afe8490a0b42 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Adwait Nayak <adwaitn@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Thu, 10 Jul 2025 12:04:04 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] UPSTREAM:DP:CP:wifi: ath12k: Add MLO 3 link simultaneous tx
 support

Currently, 3 link MLO association is supported but active
transmission with 3 links simultenously is not supported;
because TQM is designed to handle MPDU Gen and BA processing
over 2 links only. Hence, native 3 link MLO is not supported.

It is required to support 3 link simultaneous TX for MLO by
using different TIDs for different flows under same AC and
have these TIDs mapped across all 3 links (1 TID still
being mapped to 2 links).

In order to support simultaneous 3 link TX on MLO supported
chipsets, following is done:

-> In WiFi, there are 2 TIDs per Access Category.
   Using different TIDs of same AC, flow distribution can be
   achieved.
-> Map different TIDs of same AC across all 3 links to have
   all 3 links used for TX. For example, use TID0 on link 1
   and link2 while TID3 on link2 and link3.
   Using this, all 3 links can be used simultaneously
   for a given client.
   This requires minimum of 2 flows of same AC to be started.

-> The TID mapping will be done internally within FW for all
   3 link MLO peers based on link capacity.

-> It can also be done based on the user provided ranked list
   and FW will do the TID mapping across links

For 3-link Tx link management a new module param (mlo_3_link_tx)
is introduced.
This feature is only applicable for QCN9274 chipset.

